MatchName: Gujarat Titans VS Rajasthan Royals
TossDetails: Rajasthan Royals won the Toss and elected to bat
TossText: won the Toss and elected to bat
PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of the Final of the TATA IPL 2023. The tournament successfully completed its 14 years and in this 15th year, the tournament became more special in each and every aspect including the number of teams, games, and competitiveness. The 70-plus day toil of the teams comes to an end today with the top two teams Gujarat Titans and Rajasthan Royals surviving in the highly competitive tournament and it all comes to an end today with the ultimate champion being unfurled today. The Rajasthan Royals enter the finals after their first season this time and for the Gujarat Titans, this is their maiden season and final. The match today will be held at Narendra Modi Stadium, Ahmedabad. Who will turn victorious in the ultimate battle and will sit on the throne with the trophy? Will the stands with an audience of more than one lakh people echo "Aave De" or "Halla Bol"?

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

Both the teams have clashed against each other twice, once in the league stage in which Gujarat Titans won the match by 37 runs and in the qualifier one Gujarat chased down the target in the last over! Will Gujarat beat Rajasthan Royals for one last time this season or will Rajasthan rewrite the history and win in this ultimate match?

 

VENUE STATS:-

The stadium hosted the qualifier two match here and it was the team that chased the target won. The first innings total was 158 in the previous game and the fast bowlers of both the teams picked 9 wickets in total and this venue could be ideal for the pacers.

 

PITCH REPORT:- 

Simon Doull: "The bounce is a bit higher here, sticking onto the surface a little bit. Bowlers who can hit the deck hard, bowl that back of a length can cause trouble to the batters, the dimensions are pretty much the same, although one side is slightly shorter. Teams that have batted first have won the final 9 times, win the toss, bat first and put up something around 180-190."

 

TOSS:-

Rajasthan Royals have won the toss and they elect to bat first!

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Captain: "We will bat first. Looks like a good wicket, a bit dry and that's why we'll bat first, it's a used wicket and might help our spinners in the second innings. We're all positive and excited. Playing in front of this crowd is exciting. The moment we stepped into the ground we felt special. Same team for us."

 

Hardik Pandya, Gujarat Titans Captain: "We would have bowled first. This is fantastic to see so may people coming to support us. We have the opportunity to be a hero and this is the time for us. We have to approach this game as normal as possible, the boys have been very chilled out and thanks to the support staff for managing that. We have one change - Lockie Ferguson comes in place of Alzarri Joseph."
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Rajasthan Royals- 44/1 (7.3 rpo, 4x4, 2x6) || Gujarat Titans- 31/2 (5.2 rpo, 3x4, 1x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Rajasthan Royals- 50/4 (5.5 rpo, 6x4, 0x6) || Gujarat Titans- 66/1 (7.3 rpo, 5x4, 1x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Rajasthan Royals- 36/4 (7.2 rpo, 1x4, 2x6) || Gujarat Titans- 36/0 (11.4 rpo, 2x4, 2x6)

 

Gujarat Titans chase down the target against Rajasthan Royals and finish their maiden tournament as the ultimate champions. After winning the toss, RR elected to bat first. The openers Y Jaiswal and J Buttler got dismissed for 22 runs and 39 runs respectively and the GT bowlers kept on taking wickets at regular intervals. The skipper H Pandya led the team from the front with the ball as he finished his spell with 3 wickets in four over and by giving just 17 runs. With the target of 131 to chase, GT started off slowly and steadily with S Gill* (45 off 43) holding one end. H Pandya (34 off 30) played his part with the bat too and D Miller in the end made up 32* runs off just 19 deliveries and all these efforts steered the team to the victory by 7 wickets and with 11 balls to spare.

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Skipper: "This season was really special for us. Last two-three seasons all the fans, everyone was having a really hard time. Good to give them some happy moments. Really proud of my team. Great youngsters, great senior players. One off day today but really proud of my team."

 

Hardik Pandya is the Player of the match

Hardik Pandya, Skipper of Gujarat Titans and Player of the Match: "Wanted to show at the right time what I've worked hard for. Today was the day from the bowling point of view I saved the best for the best. All about sticking to the right lengths, asking the batters to play the right shots. For me my team is the most important. I've always been that kind of individual. If I were to have a worse season and my team wins, I'll take that. Batting comes first to me, always going to be close to my heart. Count myself lucky winning 5 finals, it's been exciting. This is going to be a special one. We spoke about creating a legacy. Generation to come, everyone will remember this was the team who started this journey and to win the championship first year is very special."

MatchName: Rajasthan Royals VS Royal Challengers Bangalore
TossDetails: Rajasthan Royals won the Toss and elected to Field
TossText: won the Toss and elected to Field
PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of Qualifier two in the TATA IPL 2023 where it is a Royal clash tonight with Rajasthan Royals and Royal Challengers Bangalore squaring off against each other at Narendra Modi Stadium, Ahmedabad. RR are here facing RCB as they lost their ticket to finale match and it was Gujarat Titans who entered the finals beating them. It is the second opportunity for RR to make it to the finals. Their opponents RCB are here after knocking out Lucknow Super Giants in their previous fixture. It will be nothing short of entertainment tonight! Who will turn out victorious tonight and enter the finals? 

 

VENUE STATS:-

This venue has hosted five IPL matches in the previous season and the average first innings total was 159. The venue has favoured the teams which chased the target as the teams won three times and two times by the teams defending the target.

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

Both the teams have faired off against each other 24 times and RCB have won 13 matches and RR have 11 wins. In this season, two times they have clashed and the record remains equal with 1-1.

 

PITCH REPORT:-

Matthew Hayden: " It is extremely hot here. The pockets are a little bit bigger. There are no cracks, got great even covering of grass and I expect batting is gonna be really good. Average scoring winning is 175."

 

TOSS:-

Rajasthan Royals won the toss and will bowl first!

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Skipper: "We will bowl first. The wicket is a bit sticky and hopefully it will help our bowlers first-up. Yesterday we had a good practice session. Everyone is happy and excited for the game. Important to keep calm and cut off the noise, trust yourself and just another game of cricket. No changes for us."

 

Faf Du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Skipper: "We were actually looking to bat first, it looks a good pitch and we believe runs on the board in a big game will count in our favour. Everyone has turned up really fresh and pumped up for the game. Tonight we are playing a very strong team and it is all about doing the right things. It's an amazing ground, this is my first game here and it is incredible to play in front of so many people. No changes in the XI"
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 46/1 (7.7 rpo, 6x4, 1x6)  || Rajasthan Royals- 67/1 (11.2 rpo, 6x4, 5x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 77/2 (8.5 rpo, 2x4, 4x6) || Rajasthan Royals- 59/1 (6.5 rpo, 5x4, 2x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 34/5 (6.8 rpo, 1x4, 2x6) || Rajasthan Royals- 35/1 (11.1 rpo, 1x4, 3x6)

 

Rajasthan Royals dominates Royal Challengers Bangalore and registers their spot in the finals. After winning the toss and opting to field first, RR picked the wicket of Virat Kohli within the powerplay and put up the pressure straight away. R Patidar constructed his innings and made 58 runs off 42 balls along with the quick cameo of G Maxwell (24 off 13). P Krishna and O McCoy accounted for three wickets each and restricted the total to 157 runs. RR in the chase started off brilliantly and Jos Buttler carried the innings on his shoulder and escorted the team to the victory by 7 wickets and 11 balls to spare. Rajasthan Royals will face Gujarat Titans at this same venue on Sunday for the grand finale!

 

Faf Du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Captain: "When we walked off the field, we felt were a few short. Felt 180 was a par score on that pitch. First six overs felt like Test cricket. Compared to the other wickets, this one was quicker off the new ball, and then it eased off later in the innings. Great season for RCB. Really proud. My first season coming in and seeing how special the fans are everywhere we go. A big thank you to everyone coming out and supporting us. Obviously disappointed tonight. Came up against a really strong Rajasthan team who probably deserve it more than us. Well done to everyone and thank you very much."

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Captain: "It was tough after a loss in the last game, but we are used to bouncing back in the tournament. In IPL it's very normal that you go ups and downs throughout the tournament. We lost a few games, we knew how to come back and we did really well. The wicket was a bit sticky and was helping the fast bowlers a bit, it had really good bounce and was easier playing the spinners. We closed the innings really well, having DK and Maxi at the end we knew what they could do but having belief and composure in our skills is what got us through. Very grateful to have someone like Jos, and the way he is batting, touchwood, we have one more game to go."

 

Jos Buttler is the player of the match 

Jos Buttler: "I came to the season with very low expectations but a lot of energy. It is very exciting to stand in the final. I had a season of two halves, and had very honest conversations with people really close to me. I was feeling the pressure midway, and it was only about a week ago that I opened up about it. Sometimes it is not working for me, and there are times when a younger me would have played a shot and come out. But it's something that Sanga has been saying that the longer you stay, you give yourselves a chance to find a way. Great excitement to have the opportunity to play in the final of the biggest tournament in T20 cricket."

MatchName: Lucknow Super Giants VS Royal Challengers Bangalore
Commentss: Royal Challengers Bangalore Won by 14 Runs (Qualified)
TossDetails: Lucknow Super Giants won the Toss and elected to Field
TossText: won the Toss and elected to Field
Comments: Royal Challengers Bangalore Won by 14 Runs (Qualified)
PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of the Eliminator match in the TATA IPL 2023 where the Lucknow Super Giants square off with the Royal Challengers Bangalore at Eden Gardens, Kolkata. The newbies LSG displayed an astounding brand of cricket in their maiden season and they became the second team to seal the spot in the playoffs. Their opponents for tonight, RCB set foot into the playoffs with the courtesy of Mumbai Indians defeating Delhi Capitals in their last game. Both the teams are in positive momentum after a victory in their previous match and the winner of this fixture will enter the Qualifier two and play against Rajasthan Royals. Will it be a Red rage tonight or will it be LSG who will finish high?

 

VENUE STATS:-

The Qualifier match number one that took place here witnessed 379 runs yesterday and the team which chased the target won the match. 

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

In the only time these two teams met, RCB batted first and put up a total of 181 runs and LSG fell short of 18 runs in the chase.  

 

PITCH REPORT: 

Graeme Smith: "A bit two-paced, the ball skids along and gets a little better to bat on. It's the same pitch that was used yesterday. Looks a perfect pitch for a matchup again, doesn't look like 40 overs were played here yesterday. The average score here since 2019 is 183 and the outfield is quick and pristine."

 

TOSS:-

Lucknow Super Giants won the toss and decided to bowl first!

 

KL Rahul, Lucknow Super Giants Skipper: "We will bowl first. Looks like a good wicket, we want to know what we are chasing. Hopefully we will get some swing and take few early wickets. Gowtham and Jason miss out, Krunal and Chameera come in. It is always good if the top three set up the game for your team. Hooda has playing well, and the other guys are looking forward to do well."

 

Faf du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Skipper: "We were unsure of what to do. It's a used wicket, but it looks a decent batting wicket. This ground is pretty small, so you can catch up towards the end. Siraj is back in the team. We have got some good players in the team, who thrive for this occasion. Looking forward to playing tonight."
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 52/1 (8.7 rpo, 8x4, 1x6) || Lucknow Super Giants- 62/2 (10.3 rpo, 3x4, 5x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 71/3 (7.9 rpo, 5x4, 2x6) || Lucknow Super Giants- 81/1 (9.0 rpo, 1x4, 6x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Royal Challengers Bangalore- 84/0 (16.8 rpo, 8x4, 6x6) || Lucknow Super Giants- 50/3 (10.0 rpo, 2x4, 3x6)

 

The eliminator was nerve-wracking till the end and it was Royal Challengers Bangalore who held their nerve and defended the target against Lucknow Super Giants. After winning the toss and electing to field first, LSG picked the skipper of RCB for a duck. The sole innings from Rajat Patidar (112* off 54) in the middle boosted the score and Dinesh Karthik (37* off 23) in the end did his part very well as a finisher and the total was 207! In the chase, LSG lost their opener QDK in the first over. KL Rahul (79 off 58) and Deepak Hooda (45 off 26) partnered for 96 runs and played a fighting knock. But towards the end, the other batters couldn't fire and the team lost the match by 14 runs! With this win, RCB qualifies further to Qualifier-two and will face Rajasthan Royals there on 27th.

 

KL Rahul, Lucknow Super Giants Skipper: "We let ourselves down in the field. Dropping easy catches never helps. Difference was obviously Patidar playing such a knock. When someone in the top three scores a hundred, more often the team wins. They fielded really well and we were poor. We'll take back a lot of positives. It's a new franchise. We've made a lot of mistakes, every team does that. Have to try and come back stronger. Mohsin showed everybody how good he is and what skill he possesses."

 

Faf du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Skipper: "Today was a special day. The guys put in a special performance. Over the moon. For a young guy (Rajat Patidar) to play like he did. His hundred was one of the best I have seen in the IPL. Our bowlers were clear and calm and that was good. We were very happy as a group. As a group we needed some calm presence. We didn't feel like it was a big game. Every one was calm and relaxed. Harshal bowls the important overs. Second last one over from him changed the game for us."

 

Rajat Patidar is the player of the match 

Rajat Patidar: "When I time the ball, my focus was on it. The last over of the powerplay when Krunal was bowling to me, my execution went fine then and I got confident afterwards. The wicket was pretty good and I played some good shots. I never feel any pressure as I think I have the ability to make up for the dots."

MatchName: Gujarat Titans VS Rajasthan Royals
TossDetails: Gujarat Titans won the Toss and elected to Field
TossText: won the Toss and elected to Field
PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of Qualifier one in the TATA IPL 2023 where the Gujarat Titans clash against the Rajasthan Royals at Eden Gardens, Kolkata. It has been an amazing start for the fresh team Gujarat Titans as they finish the league stage with ten wins and finished on top of the table. Their opponents Rajasthan Royals displayed a consistent brand of cricket and ended their league stage by finishing number two in the table. The winner of today's match will directly qualify for the finals and the team which loses will get another chance to enter the final through qualifier two! Will Gujarat Titans step into the finals on their maiden season or will Rajasthan get in for the first time after the inaugral season?

 

VENUE STATS:-

In the last four International T20 games played at this venue, it was the teams that batted first won three games. The average first innings score in those games was 178/6 with three 180 plus scores! This venue also holds the record of second highest sixes since 2018 IPL!

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

The two teams have faired off against each other once and GT won that match by 37 runs!

 

PITCH REPORT: 

Matthew Hayden: "It's got lots of grass cover and that means the quicks will be in play. I don't think there's going to be a lot of turn. Not much of wear and tear. Expect round about 170-180 to be a par score and expect the captains to have a bowl."

 

TOSS:-

Gujarat Titans have won the toss and have elected to bowl first!

 

Hardik Pandya, Gujarat Titans Skipper: "We will bowl first. Looks a decent track to bat on, and just want to know what we are chasing. Boys are pretty pumped up for this game. We treat this game as simple as possible and make sure you focus on what is controllable and making sure the intensity is high and aware of what the situation demands. One change - Alzarri Joseph comes in for Lockie Ferguson."

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Skipper: "We have done well batting first, looks like a decent batting wicket let's see what happens. Important to keep your focus on the present game and take care of what is controllable. We have been playing some great cricket throughout the tournament and would like to repeat it again. Like to keep it simple and maintain our standards. We are playing the same team."
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Rajasthan Royals- 55/1 (9.2 rpo, 6x4, 3x6)  || Gujarat Titans- 64/1 (10.7 rpo, 10x4, 1x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Rajasthan Royals- 68/2 (7.5 rpo, 5x4, 2x6) || Gujarat Titans- 75/2 (8.3 rpo, 7x4, 1x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Rajasthan Royals- 64/3 (12.8 rpo, 8x4, 2x6) || Gujarat Titans-  52/0 (10.4 rpo, 2x4, 4x6)

 

Gujarat Titans defeats Rajasthan Royals and becomes the first team to qualify for the finals! After RR being put to bat first by GT, Sanju Samson (47 from 26 balls) played a fiery knock in the beginning until Jos Buttler got settled. Buttler then shifted his gear and went on to hit 89 off 56. With the target of 189, Boult dismissed Saha in the second ball and put up pressure straight away. Shubman Gill (35 off 21) and Matthew Wade (35 off 30) partnered for 72 runs and steadied the innings! Hardik Pandya (40* off 27) at number four and David Miller (68* off 38) put up a 106* runs stand and guided the team to victory.

 

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Captain: "Felt good to put up that kind of total as I felt the wicket was a bit sticky and there was lot of swing in the powerplay. I think we managed to put in a good score, but I think they played really well to chase the score down. It was a bit two-paced and bounce was also not even!  We have been doing really well, the five bowlers have been our main bowlers and they have done really well throughout the tournament. We will try to come back and play some good cricket. Hoping for a good result in the next game."

 

Hardik Pandya, Gujarat Titans Captain: "Has been a constant effort through the last couple of years. All the 23 players are different characters, bring different things to the table. The kind of people we have, the genuine human beings we have. I genuinely see even the players in the dugout are trying and praying for them to make sure they do well. That is something fantastic and that is the reason we have reached where we have reached. It's all about making sure we respect this game. I'm proud of Miller for the way he has played. Wherever my team requires me to play, I don't generally demand where I want to bat. That's not how I've got success."

 

David Miller is the player of the match 

David Miller: "I've been given a role, I felt extremely backed from the outset. I'm enjoying my role, I've been playing for many years now. Understanding my game a lot better. In high-pressure situations you tend to go away from your gameplan but I feel like I'm trying to keep everything together close to the gameplan.  Backed myself and went with it. The rest I tried to hit as hard as possible."

MatchName: Sunrisers Hyderabad VS Punjab Kings

PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of Match 70 in the TATA IPL 2023, where the Sunrisers Hyderabad lock horns with Punjab Kings at Wankhede Stadium, Mumbai. This is the final match of the league stage. With these two teams falling short of qualifying, they will look to end their campaign with a positive result tonight. The team winning the match tonight will finish with 14 points. Will the sun rise or will kings sit on the throne tonight? 

Bhuvneshwar Kumar is the captain of SRH tonight!

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

The two teams have faired off against each other 19 times, and SRH leads the contest with 13 wins and PBKS with 6 wins. When the last time these two teams met this season, it was SRH who won it by 7 wickets!

 

VENUE STATS:-

Twenty matches have been played here and this is the last one here. Twelve were won by the teams bowling first and eight by the teams defending the target. 

Average 1st Innings score in each phase at the venue:-

Powerplay (1-6 Ov) :- 41/2 

Middle Overs (7-15 Ov) :- 71/2 

Death Overs (16-20 Ov) :- 54/2 

 

PITCH REPORT: 

Graeme Swann: "Equal dimensions on both sides of this ground, a factor that has helped batters score around 986 sixes this season. This is the same pitch that was used last night. The pitch is quite hard and 160 could be a good score. There will be a bit of help for the spinners."

 

TOSS:-

Sunrisers Hyderabad have won the toss and will bat first.

 

Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Sunrisers Hyderabad Captain: "We will bat first. Same wicket as the last game, so could be a bit sticky going into the second innings. Two changes, Romario Shephard is in for Kane Williamson and Jagadeesha Suchith is in for T Natarajan. We would love to win this match and go up a bit in the points table. It looks like a slow surface and we're backing ourselves to defend a score."

 

Mayank Agarwal, Punjab Kings Captain: "We have made three changes, Nathan Ellis replaces Bhanu, Shahrukh and Prerak Mankad are in, replacing Rahul Chahar and Rishi Dhawan. We don't want to make changes to the structure of the team, just giving chances to everyone. Every game is important and we're looking forward to the two points."
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Sunrisers Hyderabad- 43/1 (7.2 rpo, 6x4, 1x6) || Punjab Kings- 62/1 (10.3 rpo, 7x4, 3x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Sunrisers Hyderabad- 53/4 (5.9 rpo, 2x4, 1x6) || Punjab Kings- 94/4 (10.4 rpo, 7x4, 6x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Sunrisers Hyderabad- 53/3 (10.6 rpo, 2x4, 4x6) || Punjab Kings- 4/0 (24.0 rpo, 1x4, 0x6)

 

Punjab Kings displayed a better cricket than Sunrisers Hyderabad and finishes their campaign with a victory. SRH won the toss and elected to bat first. Abhishek Sharma (43 off 32) at the top provided a steady start and it was finished well by Washington Sundar (25 off 19) and Romario Shepherd (26* off 15). Harprit Brar and Nathan Ellis each accounted for three wickets. With 158 runs to chase, Shikhar Dhawan made up 39 runs in 32 balls. Liam Livingstone (49* off 22) was explosive right from the beginning and finished the match for their team with still 29 balls to spare!

 

Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Sunrisers Hyderabad Skipper: "Good feeling on being the captain, but it would have been better if we had won the match. I think we were a lot of runs short, but we had to field better, didn't take our chances and there were fumbles, but this was the last match of the season and that does have an effect. Have had many positives, Umran Malik and Abhishek Sharma were the obvious positives, but we have a decent core of batting with Aiden Markram and Nicolas Pooran coming up pretty well."

 

Mayank Agarwal, Punjab Kings Skipper: "There are a lot of positives for us. The way Livingstone batted, Dhawan played well. If we go out there and play the kind of cricket we play, we can do well in the next season. We couldn't stitch two back-to-back wins. We lost wickets in a cluster, and that at times derailed us. We have played an aggressive brand of cricket over all. We are going to sit and discuss now after the IPL."

 

Harpreet Brar is the Player of the Match

Harpreet Brar: "When we came here, we thought it was a good pitch for the spinners. I have conceded runs and so have the other spinners in the tournament, so I wanted to finish on a good note today. I just tried to bowl in the right areas and I wanted to keep calm under pressure. I tried to work on my skills as much as possible."

MatchName: Mumbai Indians VS Delhi Capitals
TossDetails: Mumbai Indians won the Toss and elected to Field
TossText: won the Toss and elected to Field
PreMatchCommentary:
Hello and welcome to the live commentary of Match 69 in the TATA IPL where the Mumbai Indians battle against the Delhi Capitals at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai. After 68 matches filled with ebbs and flows, there are still two teams fighting for the last playoff spot, and a team with all to lose goes up against a team that has nothing to lose. The Delhi Capitals are currently placed fifth in the points table, and their fate lies in their own hands, needing a win tonight to move them to the 4th spot, courtesy of a better NRR than the Royal Challengers Bangalore. On the other hand, RCB will be wearing blue tonight for a change, hoping that Mumbai van get the better of Delhi and help them stay in the Top 4. The Delhi Capitals have peaked at the right moment having won their last two matches, whereas Mumbai themselves have had a season to forget and will look finish on a high on their home turf.

 

HEAD TO HEAD:-

Mumbai Indians edge the Delhi Capitals in the head to head, winning 16 of the 31 games between the two sides. When the two sides met earlier this season, in what was their first matches of the season, Axar Patel and Lalit Yadav took Delhi home in the chase, as they won by 4 wickets.

 

VENUE STATS:-

Three of the last four games at the venue have been won by the chasing teams. Mumbai have won once and lost twice at this venue whereas Delhi have also won once but lost thrice.

Average 1st Innings score in each phase at night matches in the venue:-

Powerplay (1-6 Ov):- 41/2

Middle Overs (7-15 Ov):- 71/2

Death Overs (16-20 Ov):- 54/2

 

PITCH REPORT: 

Danny Morrison: "This is the middle pitch so the boundary is even on both sides. Love the red soil to pieces because it does offer bounce. Spinners do love it here. Little bit of live grass on it, but it's about getting the lengths right. Pace bowlers in particular have been bowling Test match lengths to get people out. Let's watch out for couple of wrist spinners tonight."

 

TOSS:-

Mumbai Indians have won the toss and will field first.

 

Rohit Sharma, Mumbai Indians Captain: "We are going to bowl first. Good track. Wanted to have a score in front of us. Crucial for us that we restrict them and then bat freely. We were inconsistent throughout the season. There will be a few eyes on us, so we got to come up with the best. We have tried a few things in the last few games keeping an eye on the future. We want to finish on a high. Two changes - Brevis back in for Stubbs. Shokeen in place of Sanjay, who is injured."

 

Rishabh Pant, Delhi Capitals Captain: "We wanted to bowl first. But I lost the toss, so we have to bat first. We are up for the challenge and our boys are ready for it. One change - Prithvi comes in for Lalit Yadav."
PostMatchCommentary:
Powerplay (1-6 Overs) :-

Delhi Capitals- 37/3 (6.2 rpo, 2x4, 2x6) || Mumbai Indians- 27/1 (4.5 rpo, 2x4, 2x6)

Middle Overs (7-15 Overs) :- 

Delhi Capitals- 69/1 (7.7 rpo, 3x4, 3x6) || Mumbai Indians- 74/2 (8.2 rpo, 2x4, 6x6)

Death Overs (16-20 Overs) :- 

Delhi Capitals- 53/3 (10.6 rpo, 2x4, 4x6) || Mumbai Indians- 59/2 (14.2 rpo, 5x4, 4x6)

 

Mumbai Indians successfully chase the total and end their campaign with a victory against Delhi Capitals. MI won the toss and elected to bowl first. After losing three wickets in the powerplay, Rishabh Pant (30 off 33) and Powell (43 off 34) built the innings forward and made up a total of 159 at the end of 20 overs. Tim David in the end provided the fireworks and guided the team to victory.

Kolkata Knight Riders - 44/3 (7.3 rpo) || Royal Challengers Bangalore - 36/3 (6.0 rpo)

Kolkata Knight Riders  - 27/1 (7.0 rpo) || Royal Challengers Bangalore - 39/3 (9.0 rpo)

 
Royal Challengers Bangalore gets over the line, after beating Kolkata Knight Riders by 3 wickets in a low-scoring contest. After opting to bowl first RCB struck immediately in the Powerplay, after which the lower order batters of KKR tried contributed their best to get the team to a fighting total. Wanindu Hasaranga was phenomenal with the ball with figures of 4/20. In the second innings, even after the early fall of wickets, a steady stand from Willey and Rutherford helped the team to settle, after which quick cameos from Shahbaz Ahmed, Dinesh Karthik, and Harshal Patel guided the team to the victory with four balls remaining.
 
Shreyas Iyer, Kolkata Knight Riders Captain: "I really found this game exciting. Before getting in, I spoke with my boys and told them that this game is going to define our character and attitude on the field whether we defend or not. I am really proud of the way we played this game and took it till the last over. Kudos to their batsmen, they played really well out in the middle, they took out the toughest phase as soon as possible. We are going to come back with the same mindset, we are not going to chicken out. That's what we want to focus on and that's what we spoke about coming into the tournament that we'll be someone who'd be taking risks."
 
Faf du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Captain: "Very happy, small margin games are very important at the start. Small score, we just tried to be positive but very good bowling from their seamers. The runs were never a problem, we just needed to have wickets in hand. DK is as close as it gets to MS Dhoni when it comes to being ice cool."
 
Wanindu Hasaranga is the Player of the Match
 
Wanindu Hasaranga: "I am really happy, especially with the dew it is very hard to bowl. When I go play, I don't take any pressure. That's why I feel I get successful. My favorite footballer is Neymar and that is his celebration which I do."

Rajasthan Royals defeat Sunrisers Hyderabad by 5 wickets and move to the top of the table. After being put in to bat, Rajasthan looked confident right from the beginning as they put up 58 runs in the powerplay, and impactful knocks from Samson, Padikkal and Hetmyer helped Rajasthan score 210. The Royals started the second innings with the same momentum, striking at regular intervals and restricting Sunrisers to the joint-lowest Powerplay score in the TATA IPL. The flourish of Aiden Markram and Washington Sundar was a bit too late in the end as the Rajasthan Royals won the match by a margin of 61 runs.

 

Kane Williamson, Sunrisers Hyderabad Captain: "We started beautifully with the ball, we had our opportunities. In all the games so far, there has been some swing and assistance with the new ball. You want to make some inroads, we looked very likely but unfortunately some fine margins in this game didn't go our way. It was a very good surface and Rajasthan played outstandingly well. For us, there are still a number of things to touch on and improve on as a side. You got to keep your chin up and move on to the next one. Today wasn't our day."

 

Sanju Samson is the Player of the Match

Sanju Samson, Rajasthan Royals Captain: "I think it was a different wicket than what we thought. The wicket was helping the fast bowlers if you hit the typical Test match lengths. Happy to contribute to the team's victory. Leaders like Sangakkara help me a lot. A lot of cricketing brains have gone in to pick the right side. This season we have come in with great dreams. Lot of good sides and we will take one game at a time."

Both teams will look to raise tall and make a memorable start in their new journey. This will be Hardik Pandya's first outing as captain in T20s.
PostMatchCommentary:

Lucknow Super Giants - 32/4 (5.3 rpo) || Gujarat Titans - 44/2 (7.3 rpo)

Lucknow Super Giants - 77/0 (8.6 rpo) ||  Gujarat Titans - 47/2 (5.2 rpo)

Death Overs (16-20 Ov) :-

Lucknow Super Giants - 49/2 (9.8rpo)  ||   Gujarat Titans - 70/1 (15.0 rpo)

 

With the brand new teams starting off their campaign today, the result has come in the favour of Gujarat Titans. With the toss being won by the Titans, the team decided to bowl first and struck early inside the powerplay courtesy of Shami, and he ended the match with figures of 3/25. Fifties from Deepak Hooda and the young Ayush Badoni helped Lucknow stage a comeback and post a fighting total on board. The KL-Rahul led side continued their momentum and struck twice within the powerplay, putting the brakes on Gujarat's chase. However late cameos from Rahul Tewatia and David Miller helped Gujarat score 68 in the last five overs to emerge victorious!

 

KL Rahul, Lucknow Super Giants Captain: "It was a phenomenal game to start the campaign. Starting off like that with the bat was not ideal but the way we recovered was phenomenal. It gives us so much confidence when the batters in the middle and lower order can do the job. There is so much to take away and learn for us. With the way we finished and batted in the second half we gave ourselves a chance. Good win for them and good learning for us."

 

Hardik Pandya, Gujarat Titans Captain: "This was the right game for us to be on either side and learn, but have learnt a lot by winning. Shami is known for his seam positions and he got us to a great start. We would have any day taken 160 on this wicket. Mostly I'll bat at number four, because I want to take pressure with my experience so that the others can play freely. Manohar is some talent and he is someone who you are going to hear about in the future. Tewatia was sensational as well. Getting out to Krunal would have pinched me more had we lost, but now the family is neutral and happy. He got me out and we won the match."

 

Mohammad Shami is the Player of the Match

Mohammad Shami: "I was warmed up well. It was important to get a good start in the first match, I looked to bowl a Test-match line and length here. I have worked very hard on this seam position. I try to come round the wicket to a leftie and make that angle because that's the most uncomfortable thing for them. Hardik asked me if I wanted the fourth over on the trot, but I told him to hold me back."

Punjab Kings edge Royal Challengers Bangalore in a high-scoring match as the Mayank Agarwal led side win by 5 wickets. After being put in to bat, Faf Du Plessis scored a terrific half-century in his first innings for the franchise, and cameos from Dinesh Karthik and Virat Kohli helped RCB post 205 on board. Punjab Kings started off brilliantly in the chase, putting on 71 for the first wicket, and powerful knocks from Livingstone, Odean Smtih, and Shahrukh Khan down the order helped PBKS complete their joint highest successful run chase in franchise history.

 

Faf du Plessis, Royal Challengers Bangalore Captain: "I think the batting was really good. I think we probably dropped Odean Smith on 10 and it is about the cliche of catches win watches. There was a bit of dew out there, a tough night for the bowlers, but I thought they were pretty decent with the wet ball. Small margins, but Punjab chased it down really well. The ball skidded on a bit more in the second innings and then we pulled it back beautifully. We did a lot of good things in the middle but you know what Odean Smith can do to you."

Mayank Agarwal, Punjab Kings Captain: "Two points for us is very important. Very good wicket as both sides scored 200+, one or two balls held up but nothing apart from that. Credit to the way we finished, we took the right chances and am glad it came off. Virat and Faf took the game away from us but credit to our batters to chase this down. We trust our skills. If it doesn't come off, it doesn't come off but we are not going to panic and make a scene out of it."

 

Odean Smith is the Player of the Match

Odean Smith: "We were stressing on having a good start, and we just needed to have that belief. Didn't go so well with the bowling, I need to work on a few things. Batting was good as I helped my team to win. Punjab hasn't won the title so far but we need to have the belief. We watched the movie '14 peaks', and 13 remain for us."

Delhi Capitals edge Mumbai Indians in a thriller and get off the mark in the TATA IPL 2023, after winning by 4 wickets. Having chosen to field, Kuldeep Yadav struck thrice, after which a blistering knock from Ishan Kishan helped Mumbai put 177/5 on board. In reply, a quickfire 75* (30) run-partnership for the 7th wicket between Axar Patel and Lalit Yadav helped Delhi come back and get over the line.

 

Rishabh Pant, Delhi Capitals Captain: "At the back of our minds with us losing wickets, we felt it was gone, but we just kept believing and tried to focus on the controllable. We knew we didn't have a lot of manpower with Mitch Marsh and Warner not here but we just wanted to make use of whatever we had. It is one of the best spells of Kuldeep in a long time, he was just giving it his everything in the nets and at practice. It is important to not be complacent after just one match."

Rohit Sharma, Mumbai Indians Captain: "I thought it was a good score, it didn't look like a pitch where you can get 170+ at the start but we played in the middle and finished well. Just didn't bowl according to our plans. Things didn't go according to plan but that can happen, we just need to stay close as a group and take the learnings. Disappointed with the loss but not the end."

Kuldeep Yadav is the Player of the Match.

 

Kuldeep Yadav: "It was a difficult time for me, I was out with injury for five months. It was important for me to go for the rehab and thanks to the facilities and trainers at the NCA, I recovered very well and in time to get back into the Indian setup, and slowly I started match preparation and when I started playing the games, I got the confidence and Rohit motivated me a lot. Whatever changes need to be done, I had that communication with him, and here in the Delhi set up I spoke to Ricky Ponting and he backed me a lot. I was lacking rhythm for a long time and I worked on my rhythm a lot and never compromised on turning the ball despite the variation in pace."

Shreyas Iyer starts his tourney as skipper of the Kolkata Knight Riders with a victory, after winning by 6 wickets. Having won the toss and putting CSK to bat, Umesh Yadav struck twice in the Powerplay after which MS Dhoni and Ravindra Jadeja notched up a 70 run partnership, with the former bringing up his 24th half-century in the IPL, to help post a fighting total on board. The experienced Ajinkya Rahane led KKR's chase top-scoring with 44 after which Shreyas Iyer and Sam Billings made sure Kolkata crossed the line to get off the mark in the TATA IPL 2023.

Ravindra Jadeja, Chennai Super Kings Captain: "Dew will play a vital part in this edition. If you win the toss, you will look to bowl first. The wicket was a little damp in the first 6-7 overs and then it came on nicely in the back end of the innings. We were trying to take the game deep. Everybody bowled well given the dew, especially Bravo who bowled very well."

Shreyas Iyer, Kolkata Knight Riders Captain: "There is always tension when MS Dhoni is batting. I knew momentum was going to shift towards them with the dew around as it was difficult to grip the ball. Enjoying the new franchise and the CEO, management, support staff have all been outstanding. Mumbai is one place I love to play as I grew up here. I thought the wicket would be flat but it was pretty easy for me with the bowling lineup I had. Umesh has worked hard in the nets and did well in the practice games too. Really chuffed to see him perform today."

 

Umesh Yadav is the Player of the Match for his spell of 2/20.

 

Umesh Yadav: "Wickets in the powerplay is important and the Team's role is what I carried out today. Usually I've been focusing on my rhythm and I'm thankful to my trainers for keeping me in shape."
